KANO – Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje of Kano State on Monday gave the sum of Three Million Naira (N3m) to Kano indigene, Suyudi Sani who scored aggregate marks of 303 points in the 2021 Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examinations (UTME). Suyudi Sani who hailed from Nassarawa local government area of Kano metropolis ranked the second-best in Northern Nigeria in 2021 Examinations. Dr Ganduje who honoured the youngster during the State Executive Council meeting, held at Africa House, Government House, Kano said it is the duty of the state government to help his likes achieve their goals. Fake News: Ganduje Congratulates Kano Scholar For Developing… Private: 2023: Ganduje Under Fire Over Remarks About Tinubu He said “You really did a very good thing. Ours is to always assist young people like you to achieve their goals and make their dreams reality.” Governor Ganduje revealed that “We are giving the sum of Three Million Naira (N3m) to Suyudi Sani, in addition to the state government commitment to sponsor your education up to PhD level.” In his response, Mr. Sani thanked the governor and state government for the gesture and assured that he would do his best not to disappoint the state and his family.